defs.docs: Zero-cost Futures in Rust

defs.name: Poll
defs.docs:
Return type of the `Future::poll` method, indicates whether a future's value
 is ready or not.

defs.name: Ready
defs.docs: Represents that a value is immediately ready.

defs.name: NotReady
defs.docs: Represents that a value is not ready yet, but may be so later.

defs.name: Async
defs.docs: Return type of future, indicating whether a value is ready or not.

defs.name: map
defs.docs: Change the success value of this `Async` with the closure provided

defs.name: is_ready
defs.docs: Returns whether this is `Async::Ready`

defs.name: is_not_ready
defs.docs: Returns whether this is `Async::NotReady`

defs.name: Ready
defs.docs:
The `start_send` attempt succeeded, so the sending process has
 *started*; you must use `Sink::poll_complete` to drive the send
 to completion.

defs.name: NotReady
defs.docs:
The `start_send` attempt failed due to the sink being full. The value
 being sent is returned, and the current `Task` will be automatically
 notified again once the sink has room.

defs.name: AsyncSink
defs.docs: The result of an asynchronous attempt to send a value to a sink.

defs.name: map
defs.docs: Change the NotReady value of this `AsyncSink` with the closure provided

defs.name: is_ready
defs.docs: Returns whether this is `AsyncSink::Ready`

defs.name: is_not_ready
defs.docs: Returns whether this is `AsyncSink::NotReady`

defs.name: StartSend
defs.docs:
Return type of the `Sink::start_send` method, indicating the outcome of a
 send attempt. See `AsyncSink` for more details.

defs.name: empty

Creates a future which never resolves, representing a computation that never

defs.name: Lazy
defs.docs:
A future which defers creation of the actual future until a callback is

defs.name: lazy

defs.name: err
defs.docs: Creates a "leaf future" from an immediate value of a failed computation.

defs.name: Break
defs.docs: Indicates that the loop has completed with output `T`.

defs.name: Continue
defs.docs:
Indicates that the loop function should be called again with input

defs.name: AndThen
defs.docs:
Future for the `and_then` combinator, chaining a computation onto the end of
 another future which completes successfully.

defs.name: Flatten
defs.docs:
Future for the `flatten` combinator, flattening a future-of-a-future to get just

defs.name: FlattenStream
defs.docs:
Future for the `flatten_stream` combinator, flattening a
 future-of-a-stream to get just the result of the final stream as a stream.

defs.name: Fuse
defs.docs: A future which "fuses" a future once it's been resolved.

defs.name: is_done
defs.docs:
Returns whether the underlying future has finished or not.
 
 If this method returns `true`, then all future calls to `poll`
 are guaranteed to return `Ok(Async::NotReady)`. If this returns
 false, then the underlying future has not been driven to
 completion.

defs.name: IntoStream

defs.docs: Creates a new future which will select the first successful future over a list of futures.

defs.name: Shared
defs.docs:
A future that is cloneable and can be polled in multiple threads.
 Use `Future::shared()` method to convert any future into a `Shared` future.

defs.name: peek
defs.docs:
If any clone of this `Shared` has completed execution, returns its result immediately
 without blocking. Otherwise, returns None without triggering the work represented by
 this `Shared`.

defs.name: SharedItem
defs.docs:
A wrapped item of the original future that is cloneable and implements Deref
 for ease of use.

defs.name: SharedError
defs.docs:
A wrapped error of the original future that is cloneable and implements Deref

defs.name: BiLock
defs.docs:
A type of futures-powered synchronization primitive which is a mutex between
 two possible owners.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new `BiLock` protecting the provided data.

defs.name: poll_lock
defs.docs:
Attempt to acquire this lock, returning `NotReady` if it can't be
 acquired.

defs.name: lock
defs.docs:
Perform a "blocking lock" of this lock, consuming this lock handle and
 returning a future to the acquired lock.

defs.name: reunite
defs.docs:
Attempts to put the two "halves" of a `BiLock<T>` back together and
 recover the original value. Succeeds only if the two `BiLock<T>`s
 originated from the same call to `BiLock::new`.

defs.name: ReuniteError
defs.docs:
Error indicating two `BiLock<T>`s were not two halves of a whole, and
 thus could not be `reunite`d.

defs.name: BiLockGuard
defs.docs: Returned RAII guard from the `poll_lock` method.

defs.name: BiLockAcquire
defs.docs:
Future returned by `BiLock::lock` which will resolve when the lock is
 acquired.

defs.name: BiLockAcquired
defs.docs: Resolved value of the `BiLockAcquire<T>` future.

defs.name: unlock
defs.docs: Recovers the original `BiLock<T>`, unlocking this lock.

defs.name: unsync
defs.docs: Future-aware single-threaded synchronization

defs.name: mpsc
defs.docs:
A multi-producer, single-consumer, futures-aware, FIFO queue with back
 pressure, for use communicating between tasks on the same thread.

Represents the completion half of a oneshot through which the result of a
 computation is signaled.

A future representing the completion of a computation happening elsewhere in
 memory.

defs.docs: Completes this oneshot with a successful result.

defs.docs:
Polls this `Sender` half to detect whether the `Receiver` this has
 paired with has gone away.

defs.docs:
Tests to see whether this `Sender`'s corresponding `Receiver`
 has gone away.
